args: Ah, but my friend looked simply stunning\nin her wedding dress. Perhaps someday\nI'll wear such a wonder as well...
Are you worrying overmuch about\nthe vagaries of life again?
Actually, I have marriage on my mind.
Oh no, not me. I've simply been invited\nto a great number of weddings lately.
I suppose I'm entering that time where\none friend after another exits my life\nto the sweet peal of wedding bells.
I can't help but think how wonderful the\nexperience must be, what with the fine\ndress and other assorted pageantry.

It makes me dream about experiencing
those feelings for myself someday.
...Not that I have any current plans
in that department, alas.
Here, now! You cannot simply waltz in\nwithout so much as a by your leave!
Does Cleo have guests? If so, it sounds\nlike they are being quite the handful.
We should go take a look.
This woman just barged into the castle\nand started demanding that I put aside\nwhat I was doing and help her!
It's said you castle folks are always\nhelping people, right? So are you or not?!
So why aren't you helping ME?!
Lady, we don't even know what you WANT.
My name is Emily, and I want\nall of you to help me elope!
Okay, that's not usually the\nkind of help that we—
You see, I'm in love with a wonderful man,\nbut my parents are insisting that I enter\nan arranged marriage to someone else!
Well, I'm not going to do what they want!\nI will be married to my sweet babboo\ncome hell or high water!
Ah, it's like something out of a faerie tale!\nWell, except for the ＂sweet babboo＂ part.
Wrong! The love he and I share\nis BETTER than any faerie tale!
So here's my plan: You people go out and\nfind a fake who will PRETEND to be me\nat the arranged-marriage ceremony.

Then, while you're schmoozing at the
wedding and eating cake or whatnot,
me and my sweet babboo will run away
and be married in secret!
Er, but won't the entire audience be filled\nwith your friends and family?
Surely they are going to notice that\nthis false bride is not actually YOU.
Yeah, yeah, don't worry.\nI've got that all covered.
This plan is a couple potatoes short\nof a full stew. Who the heck would\never sign on to such a batty thing?!
What's that? You'll be the fake me?\nNo takebacks, you all heard her!
Now come on, get this wedding dress on.\nLet's go, move it, move it! Me and my\nsweet babboo don't have all day!
Yep, yep, that all fits perfectly.\nNo one will ever suspect a THING!
Well, I suppose I will give it my best.
And I will make plans for my elopement.\nThaaaanks, you guys are the best! Toodles!

Goodness, what a pushy woman!
Still, it must be difficult to come from
the type of family where an arranged
marriage is expected of you.
Marriage is more of a business\narrangement than anything else\nfor folks like that.
That lady TOTALLY meant business.\n...I kinda want to be her now.
Well, as we've apparently been\npress-ganged into her service,\nI suppose we should... Er, Xania?
Wait, but what do I DO?!

Should I do something bride-y?
Perhaps a little self-improvement?
Or maybe transform myself into a totally
different person for my special day!
I fear she has lost the plot a bit.
Normally I'd say she was simply getting\ndistracted in her own way, but this does\nappear to be something more severe.
Well, she seems to be enjoying herself,\nso let's just roll with it for now.
Maybe we'll figure this whole thing out\nwhile she figures out...um, herself.
Goodness, my heart is pounding...\nBeing a bride is so INTENSE!
Are we certain she is going to be all right?
